text:
{
  "prompt": "Technical 3-view drawing of the BMW CE 04 electric scooter in blueprint style. The illustration should include a side view, front view, and top view, aligned in engineering drafting format. Key mechanical features like the long low frame, underfloor battery pack, floating seat, hub motor rear wheel, aerodynamic fairings, and digital dashboard should be clearly depicted. The drawing should resemble a concept design sheet, cleanly labeled, and suitable for analyzing aerodynamics and structure. Blueprint background with white line art.",
  "size": "1024x1024"
}

{
  "prompt": "A realistic 3D render of an electric motorcycle inspired by the BMW CE 04, with the following specifications: - Handlebar width: 800mm - Skateboard-style flat battery pack mounted on the bottom frame - Central seating layout similar to CE 04 with a slim and ergonomic one-piece seat - Front wheel: 17 inches, Rear wheel: 13 inches - Suspension: telescopic front forks and dual rear shock absorbers optimized for city potholes - Compact and aerodynamic design, urban-ready - white and red color scheme - background: clean white studio lighting for showcasing the full side profile and 3/4 front view of the vehicle. Include proportional design hints for future production (like real-size proportions of footrests, headlight height, ground clearance etc).",
  "size": "1024x1024"
}

{
  "prompt": "A technical side view illustration of a modern electric scooter designed for delivery use. The vehicle features a step-through frame with a low central tunnel to allow easy mounting and dismounting. The front wheel is 20 inches in diameter, and the rear wheel is 16 inches. The handlebars are wide (800mm), and the seat is long and slightly raised at the rear, styled like the BMW CE04. The battery is mounted in a skateboard-style flat pack along the lower frame. Front and rear suspension is visible, designed for comfort and urban road bumps. A large rear top box is mounted for cargo. The design is clean and futuristic, with emphasis on practicality and good ergonomics.",
  "size": "1024x1024"
}

{
  "prompt": "A technical side view line drawing of an electric scooter concept. The vehicle has a low, flat step-through frame for easy mounting, a large battery pack integrated as the main structural base (skateboard-style battery at the bottom), and a visibly separated rear swingarm with dual rear gas shock absorbers. The front fork is reinforced with a visible rigid structure, and the handlebar width is about 800mm. The seat design is inspired by the BMW CE04 with a floating, modern look. The overall style is sleek and urban, optimized for high-torque city commuting. The rear section is ready to mount a top box. Technical drawing style, clean lines, black on white background.",
  "size": "1024x1024"
}

{
  "prompt": "A futuristic electric scooter (motorbike-style) with a step-through frame design. The design features two slim, rectangular battery packs mounted symmetrically on the lower left and right sides of the frame, leaving the center open for easy foot passage (true step-through). The seat is styled like the BMW CE-04, floating above the main frame, and the rear swingarm has dual gas shocks. The front and rear wheels are asymmetrical: the front wheel is larger (20-inch) and the rear wheel smaller (16-inch) with street tires. The handlebar width is about 800mm, and the overall design looks sleek, aerodynamic, and city-ready. The setting is a clean technical rendering, white background, side view.",
  "size": "1024x1024"
}

{
  "prompt": "A technical side-view and semi-transparent three-quarter view drawing of a futuristic electric scooter with a step-through frame design. The design features a split battery pack: one located under the seat, and one in the front lower section, leaving the middle frame completely open for step-through functionality. The scooter uses a 96V 300Ah battery system and a central 8000W motor. Rear suspension consists of dual gas shock absorbers attached to a rear swingarm independent of the battery structure. The front fork is reinforced for urban road shock absorption. The handlebars span 800mm. The design maintains a slim, aerodynamic silhouette similar to the BMW CE 04 but emphasizes accessibility and comfort. Label visible parts for reference. Technical digital style in black and white line art.",
  "size": "1024x1024"
}

{
  "prompt": "A technical line drawing of a futuristic electric scooter in side view, designed with an extended wheelbase of over 1500mm. The design includes a fully step-through frame, low and flat for easy access, and a skateboard-style battery pack spread completely across the bottom. The rear suspension uses dual gas shocks, and the front fork is reinforced for urban road conditions. The design looks unusually long but is optimized for housing a 96V 300Ah battery. The handlebars are 800mm wide, and the front wheel is larger than the rear. The illustration is black and white with clean, sharp outlines.",
  "size": "1024x1024"
}

{
  "prompt": "A high-detail side profile technical rendering of an electric step-through scooter with a 1700mm wheelbase. The design is inspired by the long range escooter shown in the image: a flat skateboard-style battery pack fully integrated in the floor, dual rear gas shock absorbers, upright comfortable seating with a small passenger backrest, and 20-inch front wheel with 16-inch rear wheel. The frame is tubular with an industrial, rugged feel, and the step-through area is clear and low. Include front and rear LED lights, mirrors, and a utility box or platform mount behind the seat for a delivery box. Ensure the wheelbase (distance from front to rear axle) is visibly extended to match 1700mm proportionally. Render in grayscale or black and white technical sketch style.",
  "size": "1024x1024"
}

{
  "prompt": "A 3D-rendered side view of a modern electric scooter in bright yellow, designed for long-range use. The design includes a stretched wheelbase of 1700mm, and the rear wheel is moved farther from the battery pack. The battery pack is more widely spread and lower along the floorboard, creating a balanced, low-center-of-gravity design. The scooter features dual rear gas shocks, a step-through frame for easy access, large front forks for urban road bumps, and street tires on mid-sized wheels. The aesthetic resembles the previous long-range yellow escooter but with extended chassis and refined battery integration.",
  "size": "1024x1024"
}

{
  "prompt": "A high-resolution digital rendering of a futuristic step-through electric scooter. The scooter features a wide and low-slung battery pack that is spread out 15% more in all directions compared to the previous design. The rear wheel is positioned further back to extend the wheelbase and enhance ride stability. The overall frame maintains a step-through design for ease of access, with dual rear gas shock absorbers and a slightly elongated silhouette. The front features a minimalist LED headlight and slim handlebars. The color scheme is matte yellow with black accents.",
  "size": "1024x1024"
}

{
  "prompt": "A futuristic electric scooter with the following features: a low step-through frame, extended wheelbase of around 1700mm, the rear wheel hub shifted 200mm further back than standard, and a battery pack spread out widely along the deck area. The scooter includes a visible foot peg (foot rest) for the rider, a sleek aerodynamic front cowl, and a windscreen shield. The rear has a dual gas suspension setup, and the front uses telescopic forks. It has a modern, functional yet slightly rugged design suitable for urban commuting. The rendering should be in a 3D side view with realistic shadows and clean lighting.",
  "size": "1024x1024"
}

{
  "prompt": "A high-resolution side-view digital rendering of a futuristic electric scooter with a long wheelbase (~1700mm). The design includes a large, flat skateboard-style battery pack extended broadly around the base. The rear wheel is positioned significantly backward with a single rear shock absorber (single-shock suspension). The scooter retains a step-through frame for easy access, and the front features a sleek aerodynamic cowl and adjustable windscreen. The handlebar width is about 800mm, and overall styling is inspired by BMW CE 04 but adapted for a long-range delivery or utility use. The scooter should look modern, robust, and practical, with emphasis on real-world manufacturable proportions.",
  "size": "1024x1024"
}

{
  "prompt": "A 3D-rendered electric scooter designed for urban use, featuring a stylish aerodynamic design. It has a step-through frame and a sleek, elongated single-rider seat with an integrated small backrest to support the rider's lower back. Behind the seat is a compact, stylish cargo box (top box) that blends smoothly with the bike’s design, maintaining a futuristic and minimal look. The front has a sharply designed aerodynamic cowl and a windscreen. The rear wheel uses a single shock absorber. The battery pack is thin and wide, laid out skateboard-style under the footrest area. The handlebars are slightly raised, total handlebar width is about 800mm. The overall wheelbase is approximately 1700mm, with a large front wheel and a smaller rear wheel. Rendered from a three-quarter perspective in high resolution, side lighting to enhance contours, on a neutral background.",
  "size": "1024x1024"
}

{
  "prompt": "A futuristic, single-rider electric scooter with a 2000mm wheelbase. The scooter has a fully step-through frame, extremely low seat height (ideal for easy mounting), a wide and flat skateboard-style battery pack integrated in the bottom chassis, and a minimal but aerodynamic front fairing with a small adjustable windscreen. The rear section includes a sleek cargo box that doubles as a lumbar support for the rider, replacing the need for a tandem seat. The rear suspension uses a single centrally mounted gas shock. The design emphasizes urban utility, ride comfort, and long range. Shown in side profile, with matte black and neon yellow color scheme.",
  "size": "1024x1024"
}

{
  "prompt": "A 3D-rendered electric scooter design with a 2000mm wheelbase and a very low seat height. The front of the scooter features a streamlined aerodynamic cowl and windshield. The overall frame is sleek and modern with a step-through design. The front 'mouth' or intake area of the aerodynamic cowl is made significantly slimmer in both vertical and horizontal dimensions to emphasize sleekness. A stylish rear storage box is integrated into the rear structure, with a low-profile backrest for the rider that supports the lower back. The body is minimalistic and futuristic, suitable for urban commuting.",
  "size": "1024x1024"
}

{
  "prompt": "A realistic 3D-rendered electric motorcycle designed for city delivery use, shown in a full side view. It has a long wheelbase of 2000mm, a full flat step-through frame with no central tunnel, and a large, low-sitting battery pack spread across the floor like a skateboard. The front features a slim aerodynamic fairing with a short windscreen inspired by BMW CE-04 and Yamaha Morphos, with smooth air channels for reduced drag. The rear has a single-sided swingarm with a mono gas shock absorber and a stylish rear cargo box that doubles as a rider backrest. The wheels are mismatched: 20-inch front and 16-inch rear, contributing to an aggressive forward stance. The entire body is painted in matte gunmetal gray (dark gray) with subtle metallic texture. The handlebars are 800mm wide. No pillion seat, single rider only. High-resolution and realistic lighting.",
  "size": "1024x1024"
}

{
  "prompt": "A 3D-rendered digital image of a modern electric scooter or motorbike designed like an electric car skateboard platform. The vehicle features a full flat step-through design, with the battery pack integrated as a flat, wide layer in the bottom frame, similar to electric car platforms. The design includes a single rear shock absorber, aerodynamic front fairing and windshield, and minimalist styling. The seat is low and ergonomic with a stylish rear cargo box and backrest. The wheelbase is extended to 2000mm. Color: gunmetal gray. Realistic proportions and practical engineering details are emphasized.",
  "size": "1024x1024"
}

{
  "prompt": "A realistic 3D-rendered image of an electric scooter prototype featuring a 144V modular battery system arranged in a flat skateboard-style tray under the step-through floorboard. The design is highly aerodynamic, with a full aero front fairing, low seat height, and a clean, futuristic matte gunmetal gray finish. The battery modules are integrated into the chassis, maintaining a completely flat and open step-through area. The rear wheel is slightly extended backward to enhance wheelbase stability (2000mm), and the rear suspension uses a single gas shock. Rider footpegs and a small cargo box with a backrest are visible behind the seat.",
  "size": "1024x1024"
}

{
  "prompt": "A 3D-rendered digital image of a modern electric scooter with a fully flat step-through deck. The scooter features wide, fat tires with reduced diameter compared to previous versions, optimized for stability and urban commuting. It includes a sleek aerodynamic front cowl and a single rear suspension. The body is colored in matte gunmetal gray, designed for practical cargo and delivery usage. The wheelbase is approximately 2000mm, and the seat height is kept low. The battery pack is modular and arranged in a flat, platform-like structure under the deck, similar to electric car battery layouts.",
  "size": "1024x1024"
}

{
  "prompt": "A futuristic electric scooter designed with a long wheelbase (approximately 2000mm) and a fully flat step-through floor. The battery pack is modularized and mounted extremely close to the ground, resembling a car's skateboard-style EV platform. The tires are wide (fat tires) but with a moderate diameter to allow the flat floor. The scooter has a single rear shock absorber for space efficiency, and the seat is low and contoured with back support for the rider. The front features an aerodynamic fairing and an adjustable windshield. The overall color is matte gunmetal gray. The design is optimized for both aerodynamics and long-range performance, showing a blend of minimalism and technical detail.",
  "size": "1024x1024"
}

{
  "prompt": "A futuristic electric scooter with a 144V modular battery system designed for full-flat step-through access. The scooter features a very low ground clearance of about 120mm from the footrest to the ground. The floorboard is wide, flat, and cleanly integrated with the battery pack underneath, mimicking an EV skateboard platform. The front wheel is 20 inches, and the rear wheel is 18 inches, both are wide tires with slick tread for urban use. The frame has no obstruction between the seat and the handlebars, ensuring easy step-through mounting. The rear uses a single-sided suspension to allow flat foot access, and the front includes a sharp aerodynamic cowl and transparent adjustable windscreen. The seat is low, and a small lumbar support replaces the tandem seat. The color is matte gunmetal gray with black accents, viewed from a side angle, under natural light, clean background.",
  "size": "1024x1024"
}

{
  "referenced_image_ids": ["file_00000000320c61f9b77aab30e8f69f82"],
  "prompt": "Remove the crossbar or central hump in the step-through area of the electric scooter to allow for a completely flat, low step-through design. Ensure the floor area is continuous and flat from front to back, preserving the sleek, aerodynamic design.",
  "size": "1024x1024"
}

{
  "prompt": "A 3D-rendered digital image of a futuristic electric scooter with the following features: a full-flat step-through design, large 20-inch front wheel and 16-inch rear wheel, aerodynamic bodywork including front and rear fenders, matte gunmetal gray body color, ultra-low ground clearance with battery packs integrated almost flush to the ground, and enhanced aero elements for reduced drag. The scooter has a streamlined windscreen, minimalistic lighting, and is designed to house a 144V battery pack along the floor. The overall design is sleek, industrial, and performance-oriented, suitable for urban and long-distance riding.",
  "size": "1024x1024"
}

{
  "prompt": "A highly detailed technical line drawing of the rear section of a futuristic electric scooter (in Chunbong ULTRA style). It features a large flat battery pack (144V), a mid-drive electric motor, and a 7-speed internal gear system connected to the rear wheel. The wheel is a wide 16-inch tire with visible torque arm mounts. The rear suspension is a single gas shock absorber connected to a minimalist swingarm. The battery pack is slim and mounted low near the ground for a flat floor design. Only the rear section of the vehicle is shown, as if zoomed in to highlight the battery, motor, transmission, and rear wheel setup. No background, just a clean white technical illustration.",
  "size": "1024x1024"
}

{
  "prompt": "A transparent 3D cutaway perspective diagram of a high-performance electric scooter's rear drivetrain. The image shows a floor-mounted 144V battery pack with modular cells. A mid-mounted 4000W BLDC motor is connected in series to a 7-speed dog clutch-style transmission gearbox. The motor and transmission are housed in a compact casing below the seat area. The drivetrain extends via a direct driveshaft to a 16-inch wide rear wheel with aerodynamic fender. Transparent materials and section views are used to reveal the inner structure of the motor, gear set, and battery layout. The overall design follows a full-flat step-through platform and aerodynamic body style.",
  "size": "1024x1024"
}

{
  "prompt": "A technical cutaway diagram of a high-performance electric scooter drivetrain, showing a mid-drive motor connected to a 7-speed dog clutch gearbox. The system includes a 144V liquid-cooled BLDC motor, with a modular battery pack mounted flat below the full-flat floorboard. The drivetrain is connected via a belt to the rear 16-inch wide tire. The gearbox is oil-lubricated and enclosed. Labels indicate: motor, dog clutch gearbox (7-speed), belt pulley, battery module, and rear wheel. The style is clean and schematic, suitable for engineering visualization.",
  "size": "1024x1024"
}
